==Commencement==

===Hymn===
The "William & Mary Hymn" is sung at the commencement exercises by the choir of the College of William & Mary as the graduating class processes into [[William & Mary Hall]].

;Lyrics
{| class="toccolours" style="margin:auto;"
|-
! style="background:#ccc;"|Verse 1
|-
|Beneath thy trees, within thy halls, dear college we give praise to thee,<br>
|-
| style="background:#eee;"|To pledge ourselves, whate'er befalls, to pledge unfailing loyalty,<br>
|-
|Our hearts are with thee, dear William & Mary, however far we stray,<br>
|-
| style="background:#eee;"|Our noble college, hear us now, thy children sing to thee today.<br>
|-
! style="background:#ccc;"|Verse 2
|-
|Dear college old in years and fame, and richly old in honors too,<br>
|-
| style="background:#eee;"|Time shall not dull the shining name, whose gleam our songs will e'er renew,<br>
|-
|And as years go by, dear William & Mary, thy fame will never cease<br>
|-
| style="background:#eee;"|But each new year rejoice to see, thy children's praise to thee increase.<br>
|-
! style="background:#ccc;"|Verse 3
|-
|We honor thee not for our gain, but to make known thy majesty,<br>
|-
| style="background:#eee;"|Thy truth and courage that remain, however harsh the fates may be,<br>
|-
|As through troublous years, dear William & Mary, our country fought as thou hast fought,<br>
|-
| style="background:#eee;"|And won and lived, and lived to hear thy children singing to thee now.<br>
|-
! style="background:#ccc;"|Verse 4
|-
|O thou our guardian and our guide, renew our courage every hour,<br>
|-
| style="background:#eee;"|And keep thy spirit by our side, to aid us with its watchful power,<br>
|-
|Throughout all our lives, dear William & Mary, we pledge our loyalty,<br>
|-
| style="background:#eee;"|Dear college, now and evermore, thy children cry, "All hail to thee!".<br>
|}

